                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mirʼāt-i dawlat-i ʻAbbāsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مرآت دولت عباسی</title>
                     <note>Third front flyleaf, recto: note signed by C.M. Wade noting that the book was given to him by the Nawwab during his mission to Bahawulpur in 1832-3. Between third front flyleaf and f1 two notes by Wade dated 30 October 1848 are attached to bound in slips. One is concerned with the presentation of manuscripts to the Society by Wade, the other with the present MS, the provenance of which is described. The Nawwab is here named as Muhammad Khan. A history of the Dawud-putras, the family of the Nawabs of Bhawalpur, from their origin to A.H. 1224. Illuminated panel at beginning of text. Ruled margins. Headings and punctuation in red. Marginal glosses in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Sipas-i bi-qiyas mar dhati-ra ki ahadiyyat lazim bi-ust</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 659-60.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, iii, pp. 951-2.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
